# Bash Scripts Project

## Issue Tracking
We use Beads for issue tracking in this project.
- Check ready work: `bd ready`
- List issues: `bd list`
- Issue prefix: `bash_scripts-N`

## Project Context
Collection of bash utility scripts for system administration and automation.

### Development Guidelines
- All scripts must have error handling (set -euo pipefail at minimum)
- Use proper logging (log to syslog or dedicated log files)
- Include usage/help text in each script (-h/--help)
- Add comments explaining complex logic
- Make scripts idempotent where possible
- Test scripts in safe environments first

### Code Standards
- Use shellcheck for linting
- Follow Google Shell Style Guide
- Proper quoting of variables
- Use functions for reusable code
- Exit codes: 0 (success), 1 (general error), 2 (usage error)

### Common Issues to Watch For
- Missing error handling
- Unquoted variables leading to word splitting
- Missing input validation
- Hard-coded paths (use configuration or parameters)
- No logging or debugging output
- Scripts not being idempotent

## Workflow
1. Check `bd ready` for prioritized tasks
2. Review script for issues
3. Update issue: `bd update <id> --status in_progress`
4. Make changes and test thoroughly
5. Run shellcheck
6. Test in dev environment
7. Close issue: `bd close <id> --reason "description"`
